            </ul>
            <p>This provision does not waive liability for damages directly caused by Honest Drain &amp; Sewer LLC's gross negligence or willful misconduct.</p>

            <h2>23. Right to Refuse or Stop Service</h2>
            <p>Honest Drain &amp; Sewer LLC reserves the right to refuse or stop work when conditions are unsafe, unsanitary beyond reasonable service conditions, outside the company's scope, not properly authorized, abusive, threatening, illegal, or likely to cause unreasonable risk.</p>

            <h2>24. Customer Cancellation Rights</h2>
            <p>Certain consumer transactions may be subject to cancellation rights under federal or state law.</p>
            <p>Honest Drain &amp; Sewer LLC will comply with applicable cancellation laws where required. Emergency service, customer-requested immediate service, scheduled service, and repair work may be treated differently depending on the facts and applicable law.</p>

            <h2>25. Disputes and Opportunity to Inspect</h2>
            <p>The customer agrees to notify Honest Drain &amp; Sewer LLC promptly of any concern, dispute, or claimed issue related to the work.</p>
            <p>Honest Drain &amp; Sewer LLC must be given a reasonable opportunity to inspect the issue before the customer hires another contractor or performs additional work, unless an immediate emergency prevents doing so.</p>

